Definition:
	Variables are containers which store a single value inside memory.

Syntax:
	Data_type name = value;

Naming Conventions:
	int numOne;
	int num_one
	const int NUM_ONE
	private int _numOne
	private int _num_one

Common Types:
	integers:	int
	double:		double
	float:		float
	characters:	char
	string:		string

Examples:
	int num1 = 1;
	string stuff = "Hello World!";
	char c = 'c';
	double = 5.25;
	float = 5.25f;
